acrssvn@gmail.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alex Choi in Oshkosh, Wisconsin with @i_shipanycar, @boris__gpp, @dukedynamics, @ssrperformance, @goldenpeaksproductions, @amber_blonigan, and @inozetek. May be an image of car and road.

node.text:
Filmed my Unicorn V4 reveal video with @radaerosports and @goldenpeaksproductions and I can proudly say it will be the greatest video I’ve ever made. I can’t wait to post/ reveal it and make my comeback on youtube!
The only way we could get a camera car to keep up with 2 AIRPLANES and a lambo was another super car, so this was our solution 😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alex Choi on June 18, 2021. May be an image of car and road.

node.text:
The alternator on the 720s broke, so we rigged some extra batteries and charged them along the way like a tesla, and made it another 200-250 miles. When we were only an hour out from our destination, with no warning, every electrical component on the car went black, and not even a fully charged battery was able to turn the car back on. After being on the side of the road for 6 hours, unfortunately the 720s is being sent back to LA.
I needed a car to finish @goldrushrally , so in a very untimely way, I present you my new car, the Fiat 500 Abarth that i bought about 30 minutes away from where the car broke down.

node.text:
Here’s my new temporary wrap on the #MCDDY for @longtailrally and a few other rallies this month before I get my widebody kit! I wrapped her by myself in my garage all of last week, using @inozetek Cherry Blossom Pink, to try out a retro look on this car. Thank you @ar_motorwerkz for building these wheels to match the retro theme, and thank you @iamted7 for these amazing photos shot at an airstream park in Yosemite. Also thank you @tirestickers for doing the @michelinusa PS4S’s last minute.
We’ll call this, MCDDY V2.1, since a wrap and wheels don’t count as a “build” unlike what many other people believe. 😉
